## Authentication

The provider authenticates in this order — the first credential found wins:

1. The `api_key` provider attribute.
2. The `FROSTMOLN_API_KEY` environment variable.
3. An existing `fm` CLI session in `~/.fm/config.yaml` (enabled by default; set `use_cli_config = false` to disable). The provider uses the CLI's stored API key if present, otherwise its OIDC access token — transparently refreshing it (and writing the rotated token back to the CLI config) when it expires.

This lets the provider "just work" after `fm auth login`, like `kubectl`, `aws`, and `gcloud`. See the [Authentication guide](guides/authentication.md) for all three modes, precedence, contexts, and CI usage.

